        "comment_id": null,
        "body": "## PLAN-EVAL Verdict — #167 scaffolder hardening\n\n**Verdict: 
`FAIL_PLAN`** — implementation must NOT begin until the listed fixes are 
made.\n\nThe plan is well-researched, slices are appropriately scoped, and the 
single-source Zod→JSON Schema claim is sound (verified `zod@4.4.3` ships 
`z.toJSONSchema()`; `.strict()` semantics and `parsePluginManifest` 
non-stripping confirmed at `packages/plugin/src/protocol/manifest.ts:174,243`). 
However, the plan has a **CI wiring gap** that will silently nullify the gate it
introduces (`arch:check` is not currently in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`), an 
uncommitted `$schema` tolerance decision, an underdetermined version-coherence 
`release:cut` extension, and an under-bound S5 acceptance gate.\n\n### 
Spot-checks performed\n- `zod@4.4.3` exports `toJSONSchema()` ✅\n- 
`PluginInstallerManifestSchema` is `.strict()` (rejects `$schema`) ✅\n- 
`parsePluginManifest` does NOT strip `$schema` before `safeParse` ✅\n- JSON 
text-imports of `deno.json` work from published `@netscript/cli` tarball 
(precedent at `jsr-specifiers.ts:5`, `editor-config.ts:9`) — primary path of 
decision 4 is plausible ✅\n- `release:cut` (`findVersionResidue` + 
`bumpVersion`) walks `deno.json`, `deno.lock`, `scaffold.plugin.json`; 
residue-scan extension is feasible ✅\n- `arch:check` is NOT in 
`.github/workflows/ci.yml` — verified `ci.yml` line-by-line (only `check`, 
`test`, `lint`, `fmt:check`, `check:scaffold-versions`, `publish:dry-run`, 
`audit:critical`, `deps:latest`) ⚠️\n\n### Required fixes (most important 
first)\n\n1. **CI gate wiring.** Add an explicit step in 
`.github/workflows/ci.yml` that runs `deno task arch:check` (which will now 
include `plugins:check`). Without this, `plugins:check` is local-only and #156's
CI-enforced requirement is unmet. Promote `arch:check` from local-only to CI in 
the same commit.\n\n2. **`$schema` tolerance: pre-commit to 
strip-before-parse.** Update decision 2 to commit to: strip `$schema` (and only 
`$schema`) before `PluginInstallerManifestSchema.safeParse()` in CLI validator 
call sites (`fetch-jsr-plugin-validator.ts:90` and any other JSR/HTTPS fetch 
path). Do NOT add `$schema` as an optional field to the canonical published 
schema — that widens the published protocol. Strip is localized, deterministic, 
and preserves `parsePluginManifest` semantics.\n\n3. **Version-coherence 
single-source: bind `release:cut` deterministically.** Update decision 4: if the
prod userland-install e2e (S4) proves the JSON text-import of plugin's own 
`deno.json` resolves at scaffold-runtime from a published JSR tarball → adopt 
the primary path; record in `drift.md`; do NOT extend `release:cut` to a new 
file. Otherwise, adopt the fallback (`src/scaffold/version.ts`) AND extend 
`findVersionResidue()` + `bumpVersion()` to cover that path. The residue-scan 
regex must be updated in the same S4 commit as the source-of-truth 
decision.\n\n4. **Bind S5 acceptance gate explicitly.** S5 must require, before 
commit: (a) `deno task check`, (b) `deno task lint`, (c) `deno task fmt:check 
--ext ts,tsx`, (d) `deno task test` (full repo — catches plugin-registry 
regressions from dead-code removal), (e) `deno task e2e:cli run scaffold.runtime
--cleanup --format pretty` (catches userland-install regressions). Static 
\"unused-export\" tools cannot reliably detect dynamic imports or 
plugin-registry lookups, so behavior tests are required.\n\n5. **jsr-audit 
publishability for the additive schema asset.** Document in plan § Decisions 
that `packages/plugin/schema/scaffold.plugin.schema.json` will be added to 
`packages/plugin/deno.json` publish.include, and optionally re-exported as 
`./schema` (`\"./schema\": \"./schema/mod.ts\"` or a barrel file) so plugin 
authors can reference the canonical URL form (`jsr:@netscript/plugin/schema`) 
for `$schema` in JSR-published userland manifests. Consistent with the asset 
doctrine (`@netscript/cli` precedent at `assets/schema/**/*.json`).\n\n6. 
**Mandate a Zod↔JSON-Schema round-trip test in S1.** Add to S1: (a) 
`parsePluginManifest` accepts the 5 committed manifests (regression guard), (b) 
regenerating the schema and feeding it back through `parsePluginManifest` is 
byte-stable for valid input, (c) an invalid manifest with extra unknown keys 
fails. Addresses the \"Debt / risk\" entry on zod→json-schema fidelity 
concretely instead of deferring it.\n\n### Notes\n- Plan's slice count (5) is 
comfortable and well-shaped; all 6 fixes are tweaks, not redesigns.\n- zod v4 
`toJSONSchema()` fidelity is generally strong for the constructs used 
(`z.string`, `z.number`, `z.boolean`, `z.enum`, `z.record`, `z.array.readonly`, 
`.strict()`, `.literal`, `.refine`). The `isSafeExportPath` refine will 
serialize as a `format`/`pattern` annotation — sufficient for editor 
IntelliSense even though `parsePluginManifest` retains the refine check at 
runtime.\n- Lock hygiene preserved: no `deno.lock` or source churn from this 
evaluator session.\n\nAfter the generator revises the plan to address these 6 
fixes, re-trigger PLAN-EVAL for a fresh cycle. (Per protocol, two `FAIL_PLAN` 
cycles are allowed before escalating to the user.)"
      }
    ]
    

