(verified `zod@4.4.3` ships `z.toJSONSchema()`), and the slices are 
appropriately sized — but it has a **CI wiring gap that would silently nullify 
the gate it introduces**, an uncommitted `$schema` tolerance decision, an 
underdetermined version-coherence `release:cut` extension, and an under-bound S5
acceptance gate.

